snippet.textDisplay:
I've seen a few of your videos now that pop-up on my timeline but this one gets a sub from me. (for whatever that's worth with nearly a million. lol)

From a "kinda" strongman living in a Crossfit world: kudos to you for stepping outside of your comfort zone and actually trying something new and crushing it. As the guy in the video stated, that's what Crossfit is all about. It forces you to become a more rounded athlete with, ultimately, is a healthier version of whomever you are.

So many people in similar shoes are quick to discount Crossfit and similar types of working out w/o ever even trying it once. At least Crossfit takes the time on the front end to try to teach people proper movement and form which is far more than I can say for any other "tradition" gym I've visited over the decades. Is there bad form by some Crossfitters? Sure. Have I also seen bad form by weight lifters and powerlifters? Heck yes! It all depends on the gym/box you go to and we need more like the one I go to that make it priority #1 to teach proper form and technique and value this over all else to include scores and PRs.


But, I digress.

Thank you for making this content and showing that there is quite a bit of technique and heart required to do Crossfit well. It's high time we all supported each other regardless of your means of activity and health. Stay positive and I wish you continued success in everything you do!

"Doomed is the world where it becomes taboo to mock people who are fat and lazy but encourage those who mock others choice of fitness." -worlds_okayest_crossfitter
